gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Nuggets 113, Knicks 100
gameRecap.excerpt: The Nuggets defeated the Knicks, 113-100. Michael Porter Jr. led the Nuggets with 31 points and eight rebounds as Nikola Jokic tallied the 22nd triple-double of his season with 30 points, 14 rebounds, and 11 assists. Jamal Murray totaled 23 points, six rebounds, and four assists in the win as well. Jalen Brunson led New York with 26 points and nine assists while Isaiah Hartenstein added a career-high 20 points, along with eight rebounds and two blocks. Denver has now won seven of their last eight and are 13-2 since the All-Star break as they improve to 49-21 on the year as the Knicks have a four-game win streak snapped, so they fall to 41-28 on the year.
